      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:4:69:1",
      "text": [
        " وَقْتُ الظُّهْرِ يَوْمَ الْجُمُعَةِ حِينَ تَزُولُ الشَّمْسُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Al Fazl Bin Sh<span class=\"iTxt\">Azaan</span>, from Hammad Bin Isa, from Rabie and Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al Husayn, from Usman Bin Isa, from Sama’at, altogether, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The time for Al-Zohr on the day of Friday is when the sun (starts to) decline’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Muhammad ibn ’Isma‘il has narrated from al-Fadl ibn Shadhan from Hammad ibn ‘Isa from Rib‘i and Muhammad ibn Yahya from Muhammad ibn al-Husayn from ‘Uthman ibn ‘Isa from Sama‘ah all who has said the following: “Abu ’Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that Abu ’Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘The time of al-Dhuhr on Friday begins at Zawal (declining of the sun toward the west at noontime).” "
        ]
      }
    },
